/*You are familiar with producing output using CPP. In this task, you'll be required to write three messages in three separate lines. Write Hey hello bye. But wait a minute!! You need to write each word of it in a separate line.
Output each word of Hey hello bye in a separate line.
Hint: endl might be useful here!

Input:
No input

Output:
Hey 
hello 
bye

Explanation:
First word of the statment is in first line, next word is in next line, and last is in last line.*/

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
int main() {
  cout << "Hey"<<endl<<"hello"<<endl<<"bye";
}
